window.docContents[176].resolve({"/Class-Field-Theory-and-Galois-Theory/Local-fields-and-complete-discrete-valuation-rings/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Class-Field-Theory-and-Galois-Theory--Local-fields-and-complete-discrete-valuation-rings":{"contents":"The LocalClassFieldTheory project (Birkbeck) formalises the foundational theory of nonarchimedean\nlocal fields and their ramification, following Serre's Local Fields: complete discrete valuation\nrings, the unique extension of a discrete valuation to a finite extension, the identification of the\nintegral closure with the unit ball, and the two flavours (mixed and equal characteristic). It does\nnot contain the local reciprocity map; the cohomological construction of local reciprocity is the\nsubject of the Buzzard project in the next section. The core files are sorry-free.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Class Field Theory and Galois Theory","header":"4.5. Local fields and complete discrete valuation rings","id":"/Class-Field-Theory-and-Galois-Theory/Local-fields-and-complete-discrete-valuation-rings/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Class-Field-Theory-and-Galois-Theory--Local-fields-and-complete-discrete-valuation-rings"},"/Fermat___s-Last-Theorem-and-Regular-Primes/Reduction-to-modularity/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Fermat___s-Last-Theorem-and-Regular-Primes--Reduction-to-modularity--Reduction-of-Fermat___s-Last-Theorem-to-Modularity":{"contents":"(Reduction of Fermat's Last Theorem to modularity.)  holds. Equivalently, there is no Frey package (): a counterexample to Fermat's Last Theorem would yield a Frey curve whose mod  Galois representation is simultaneously irreducible and not irreducible.\nFormalised in FLT: Wiles_Taylor_Wiles — in progress; the top-level statement is reduced to the Mazur and Wiles inputs.\n\nReduce to a prime exponent  (, , ). A counterexample produces a Frey package and its Frey curve (). Its mod  representation  is irreducible by Mazur's theorem () yet not irreducible by the Wiles–Taylor–Wiles modularity theorem (); the contradiction FreyPackage.false shows no Frey package exists. In the Imperial formalisation the top result Wiles_Taylor_Wiles : FermatLastTheorem is assembled from these two inputs (apply Wiles_Frey; exact Mazur_Frey), which remain to be discharged.\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Fermat's Last Theorem and Regular Primes\u0009Reduction to modularity","header":"8.14.5. Reduction of Fermat's Last Theorem to Modularity","id":"/Fermat___s-Last-Theorem-and-Regular-Primes/Reduction-to-modularity/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Fermat___s-Last-Theorem-and-Regular-Primes--Reduction-to-modularity--Reduction-of-Fermat___s-Last-Theorem-to-Modularity"}});